But there are good reasons for thinking that the poem is merely playful, intended to mock the extravagant schemes of Septimius. Put shortly, the argument is as follows: ‘Septimius, you would follow me to Gades or the Cantabri or Syrtes: but the journey to Tibur (a few miles) is quite enough of' travelling and campaigning for me, sor Ι am sick of them.' It is to be remembered that Horace was, at the time when this ode was published, only 4¹ (see lutrod. p. xvii) and still far from senecta.
